ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

1. How well do you understand your child's development?
Notes: 1 = We are just beginning to understand our child's development; 2 = Between 1 and 3; 3 = We have a basic understanding of our child's development, but still have a lot to learn; 4 = Between 3 and 5; 5 = We have a pretty good understanding of our child's development; 6 = Between 5 and 7; 7 = We understand our child's development very well

ElementDescription: Something you would like written into your IFSP as an outcome for your family
2. How much do you know about your child's special needs?
Notes: 1 = Right now we do not know very much; 2 = Between 1 and 3; 3 = We have learned some things, but still have a lot of unanswered questions; 4 = Between 3 and 5; 5 = We know a lot, but still need or want to know more; 6 = Between 5 and 7; 7 = We are confident that we know most of what we need to know right now
